character.name:
Zero is not human — he is a sentient data construct created from fragmented code. His design mixes sleek sci-fi armor, glitch effects, and energy-based anatomy.

Silhouette Shape:

Slim but agile body

Slightly larger head with angular helmet

Visible glowing lines running across body like digital circuits

Back-mounted energy node (“Core Reactor”)

Color Palette:

Primary:

💠 Neon Cyan (#25E3FF)

💠 Digital Blue (#0FA1D2)

Secondary:

Dark Steel (#1B2B37)

Shadow Navy (#0A1016)

Highlight FX:

White Glow (#DFFFFF)

Glitch Magenta (#F03AE2) used for distortion abilities

🪖 2. HEAD & HELMET DESIGN
Helmet Shape:

Angular “visored” helmet

Split visor glowing cyan

Two small side modules with pulsing lights

Thin antenna-like strip on top (digital signal indicator)

Face/Visor Animation:

Horizontal scan-line shader effect

Color shifts slightly during abilities (cyan → white → magenta)

🦾 3. BODY DESIGN
Torso:

Smooth armor plates

Central “Core Reactor” glowing through the chest

Two diagonal glowing circuit lines flowing outward

Arms:

Sleek segmented armor

Forearm emitters (used for Pulse, Dash, etc.)

Fingers slightly blocky but expressive

Legs:

Long, agile proportions

Shin plates with dynamic light strips
